picked me?
What?

26:40.760 --> 26:43.593
I'm the one who knows
how to organize,
keep secrets,

26:43.600 --> 26:45.397
and do everything
betterthan he everwill.

26:45.400 --> 26:46.469
Hold on!

26:46.480 --> 26:48.198
Do none of your species
have brains?

26:48.200 --> 26:51.590
Proudly, mine does not.
Not even a nervous system.

26:51.760 --> 26:55.309
A talking plant?
That is so awesome!

26:56.280 --> 26:59.192
There's intelligent life
on this world after all!

26:59.920 --> 27:02.480
Wait a minute.
I'm intelligent life!

27:02.480 --> 27:03.959
We don't have
a minute, Rod.

27:03.960 --> 27:05.871
Not if we don't
want your mom
coming up here,

27:05.880 --> 27:07.552
and wondering where we are.

27:07.560 --> 27:09.790
And I'm good
at things, like...

27:09.800 --> 27:12.758
Look, Rod and I
have to show up
for our evening meal,

27:12.760 --> 27:15.718
butwe'll be right back
to work out a real plan
to keep you safe.

27:16.200 --> 27:17.349
Don'tjust stand there.

27:17.360 --> 27:20.909
We have to keep up
our appearances,
and I am the expert at that.

27:24.200 --> 27:25.235
Don't worry.

27:25.440 --> 27:27.635
I got your back.
I have everybody's back.

27:27.800 --> 27:30.633
Back?
I've got my back.

27:30.640 --> 27:32.995
I'm not quite sure
what she means.

27:35.920 --> 27:39.708
There is something more
we must tell you
about our presence here.

27:39.720 --> 27:41.073
We are on a mission.

27:41.080 --> 27:44.516
Yeah, Captain Grakker
said to prevent total
planetary disaster.

27:44.840 --> 27:48.230
At the hand of
the Galaxy's Most Evil
Wanted Criminal, B'KR.

27:48.240 --> 27:50.595
B'what?
B'KR. Pay attention.

27:50.600 --> 27:53.637
On yourworld,
B'KR is in disguise.

27:53.640 --> 27:55.835
To move more easily
among your kind,

27:55.840 --> 27:58.957
slowly and surely,
laying his plans
against you.

27:58.960 --> 28:00.837
What kind of disguise
are we talking here?

28:00.840 --> 28:03.308
According to our
monitoring sources,

28:03.320 --> 28:06.630
he is hiding here
under the name "Beck-Er."

28:06.640 --> 28:09.837
Becker? Billy Becker's
father is an alien?

28:10.040 --> 28:13.112
You know this
bipedal meat-pod?

28:13.120 --> 28:17.477
I know his kid.
He goes to my school.
He's gotta be adopted.

28:17.480 --> 28:21.598
Gaining the trust
of the child could help us
to investigate the father.

28:21.840 --> 28:24.274
Billy Becker might
say he trusts you,

28:24.280 --> 28:27.192
but only to get close enough
to smash a bug
on your forehead.

28:27.960 --> 28:28.949
Feels disgusting.

28:30.240 --> 28:31.593
Tastes even worse.

28:31.840 --> 28:35.515
My cousin, Venus Claptrap,
would disagree,
but moving on...

28:36.840 --> 28:38.239
Deputy Allbright,

28:38.240 --> 28:41.357
Madame Pong and I
will accompany you
to school tomorrow,

28:41.680 --> 28:45.514
and ifanything goes wrong,
the Galactic Patrol will
hold you accountable,

28:45.520 --> 28:48.080
and you will stand trial
foryour crimes.

28:48.080 --> 28:51.436
The Patrol does not
take the loss
of its agents lightly.

28:51.440 --> 28:54.034
Thanks. I'm sure
I'll sleep much better
tonight knowing that.

28:54.440 --> 28:57.352
In the meantime. Elspeth,
would you be so kind
as to continue

28:57.360 --> 29:01.956
to oversee security perimeters
and the operations
within Rod's house?

29:01.960 --> 29:04.110
What? Like you're not
gonna rememberthat?

29:04.120 --> 29:05.553
It's not for me.

29:05.560 --> 29:08.279
It's forwhen
something goes wrong
at your school tomorrow,

29:08.280 --> 29:09.349
because it will.

29:09.640 --> 29:14.919
I'll need these notes
to testify at
your trial, Deputy.

29:18.560 --> 29:21.279
Hey, Mickey.
Hey, Rod.

29:21.480 --> 29:23.948
How are your
imaginary aliens?

29:24.880 --> 29:27.838
Did he say "aliens"?

29:27.840 --> 29:30.991
I never said anything
about imaginary aliens.

29:31.000 --> 29:32.797
Well, not "imaginary."

29:32.800 --> 29:35.837
You said that
they were really small,
and they had, like, ray-guns.

29:35.840 --> 29:37.558
That's it.
I'm ventilating
his skull.

29:37.560 --> 29:40.870
Raz. Raz. Raz.

29:42.240 --> 29:44.231
Buddy, I thought
we'd talked about this.

29:45.160 --> 29:48.436
Oh. Pudge-Boy.
Just finishing up here.

29:52.320 --> 29:55.835
Right in there.
Same time tomorrow, Raz?
Can't I get a day off?

29:56.080 --> 29:59.038
Yeah, sure, whatever.

30:03.360 --> 30:05.237
Where was I?
Oh, yeah.

30:05.240 --> 30:08.277
Pudge-Boy! You'rejust in...

