31:14.720 --> 31:18.269
The Basic Drake Equation
combines all your
favorite subjects.

31:18.280 --> 31:21.511
Statistics,
Astronomy, Chemistry,

31:21.520 --> 31:24.592
and Biology.

31:24.600 --> 31:28.434
It's a way for us to think
about how many worlds
orbiting other suns

31:28.440 --> 31:32.592
might have
extraterrestrial civilizations
we could communicate with.

31:33.000 --> 31:37.278
Astronomers know
the first few numbers
to put into the equation.

31:37.280 --> 31:39.953
These numbers give us
a good estimate

31:39.960 --> 31:42.349
of the number of
Earth-like planets

31:42.360 --> 31:45.397
there are in our galaxy.

31:46.120 --> 31:48.793
Now, we get to the part
of the equation

31:48.800 --> 31:51.792
where we have to make
some educated guesses,

31:51.800 --> 31:56.794
and these guesses
involve the difference
between Chemistry and Biology.

31:56.800 --> 32:01.954
First, of these
40 billion potentially
Earth-like planets,

32:01.960 --> 32:04.235
how many have life?

32:08.120 --> 32:12.272
Just having simple Iifeforms,
like bacteria, or plants,

32:12.280 --> 32:14.555
or even small animals
isn't enough.

32:14.720 --> 32:18.156
So, then of those
earth-like planets,

32:18.160 --> 32:20.230
how many have
intelligent life?

32:24.040 --> 32:27.635
And then,
of those planets
with intelligent life,

32:27.640 --> 32:30.518
how many go on
to develop radio,

32:30.520 --> 32:35.196
or other means
of communication that
we can detect from Earth?

32:35.760 --> 32:40.276
Remember that humans lived
on Planet Earth
for millions of years

32:40.280 --> 32:44.034
before we invented
radio and television,

32:44.040 --> 32:46.508
and then lasers
for sending signals.

32:46.520 --> 32:48.158
And who knows.

32:48.160 --> 32:50.674
Maybe there are
still incredible
communication technologies

32:50.680 --> 32:52.113
that we know
nothing about today,

32:52.120 --> 32:54.680
because we can't imagine them.

32:54.680 --> 32:57.274
But they will he invented
sometime in the future.

32:57.280 --> 33:00.397
Maybe even by one of you.

33:00.400 --> 33:04.075
Depending on the numbers
used in the last parts
of the equation,

33:04.480 --> 33:07.631
we get a range of
possible answers,

33:07.640 --> 33:09.676
so that the Drake
Equation tells us

33:09.960 --> 33:13.430
the number of possible
extraterrestrial civilizations

33:13.440 --> 33:18.753
can be anywhere
from one, ours,
to more than 30 million!

33:18.760 --> 33:23.151
Whatever the true answer
to the Drake Equation
turns out to be,

33:23.160 --> 33:26.470
a big number
into the hundreds
of thousands,

33:26.480 --> 33:29.472
or a small number
that you can count
on your hands...

33:29.480 --> 33:30.549
Yes!

33:30.560 --> 33:32.710
...orsimply one,
it will be something

33:32.720 --> 33:34.472
that will change
our understanding

33:34.480 --> 33:37.438
of the universe
as we now know it.

33:37.440 --> 33:42.116
As the famous
science-fiction writer,
Arthur C. Clarke, once said,

33:42.120 --> 33:44.839
"Sometimes I think we're
alone in the universe,

33:44.840 --> 33:47.195
"and sometimes
lthink we're not.

33:47.200 --> 33:50.590
"In either case,
the idea is quite staggering."

33:55.520 --> 33:56.999
All right, class,

33:57.000 --> 33:59.355
