Phil here Is on
a quest for his roots.

34:49.120 --> 34:50.599
I'm working
my asparagus off.

34:52.239 --> 34:53.514
How about you?

34:53.520 --> 34:58.275
Warrior Science compels
all who are able to protect
those who are not.

34:58.560 --> 35:00.994
But ifyou all join
for different reasons,

35:01.000 --> 35:04.436
doesn't that make you
all argue about what to do
and how to do it?

35:04.600 --> 35:08.957
Cleveryoungling.
A healthy differing of
opinions is as necessary

35:08.960 --> 35:11.758
as the frelnik
and groof in spring.
Well said.

35:11.760 --> 35:13.034
Okay.

35:13.040 --> 35:15.429
As you can see,
despite our differences,

35:15.440 --> 35:18.591
the Ferkel's crew
are united as members
of the same team,

35:18.600 --> 35:20.955
helping each other
to accomplish
our mission,

35:20.960 --> 35:22.837
just like you
and your cousin.

35:22.840 --> 35:25.035
What? Rod and me?

35:25.040 --> 35:26.632
We're not on any team.

35:26.640 --> 35:29.473
Young Elspeth,
you must ignore
the confusing surface,

35:29.480 --> 35:31.471
and dig down to find
the truth beneath it.

35:31.800 --> 35:34.917
That Is where
you will discover
what unites you with Rod.

35:34.920 --> 35:37.480
Yeah, like cracking open
a weird-looking nut shell

35:37.640 --> 35:39.596
to find the good
stuff inside.

35:39.920 --> 35:41.399
Think on that,
young Elspeth,

35:41.400 --> 35:45.598
and you will see what
connects you with Rod
instead of what does not.

35:45.600 --> 35:48.558
Iguess
it wouldn't hurt to...
Hold on.

35:48.560 --> 35:50.232
What's that?
Uh, the Ferkel?

35:50.240 --> 35:52.231
It's only been there,
